<div id="review_3558927288" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3558927288" />
    <a title="Dipalee Joshi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/96676592-dipalee-joshi"><img alt="Dipalee Joshi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1557490967p2/96676592.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3558927288?book_show_action=true">Sep 20, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dipalee Joshi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dipalee Joshi" href="/user/show/96676592-dipalee-joshi">Dipalee Joshi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3558927288" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1458823939666171711">The Merchant of Stories is a remarkable personal diary and biographical book that not only covers Dipa Sanatani’s own family history, but also her journey of being a writer and an entrepreneur. It&apos;s an amazing story of ambition, family heritage and tenacity - over many generations. She also talks about her ancestor&apos;s fascinating story of immigration, adaptation, and melding cultures. She weaves the tales of her family with her own journey.<br/><br/>Dipa Sanatani manages to bring her personality onto these</span>
  <span id="freeText1458823939666171711" style="display:none">The Merchant of Stories is a remarkable personal diary and biographical book that not only covers Dipa Sanatani’s own family history, but also her journey of being a writer and an entrepreneur. It's an amazing story of ambition, family heritage and tenacity - over many generations. She also talks about her ancestor's fascinating story of immigration, adaptation, and melding cultures. She weaves the tales of her family with her own journey.<br /><br />Dipa Sanatani manages to bring her personality onto these pages while seriously teaching about what it means/takes to be a 'Girlboss'. The balance between the casual narration style and unerring business and writing advice is fantastic.<br /><br />The Merchant of Stories follows Dipa Sanatani’s journey through writing a wonderful book 'The Little Light', successful publishing business and life. She’s inspiring and definitely offers a lot of sound advice for aspiring writers. The author has a great outlook on life and the book inspires you to have more confidence in yourself, even if you feel like you are failing at what you think you should be doing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1458823939666171711" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
