  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3488390359" />
    <a title="Shubh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/98952316-shubh"><img alt="Shubh" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3488390359?book_show_action=true">Aug 10, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shubh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shubh" href="/user/show/98952316-shubh">Shubh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3488390359" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4027128347224059639">A determined entrepreneur&apos;s journey of identity, culture, heritage and home.<br/><br/>I thoroughly enjoyed reading this second book after Dipa Sanatani&apos;s, &quot;The Little Light!&quot; It gives the reader a glimpse of the author&apos;s journey with personal anecdotes and stories, along with some useful tips for those looking to self-publish. While mainly applicable for those in the publishing business, some portions are clearly relatable for those who have operated or worked in a start-up. It covers some of the internal</span>
  <span id="freeText4027128347224059639" style="display:none">A determined entrepreneur's journey of identity, culture, heritage and home.<br /><br />I thoroughly enjoyed reading this second book after Dipa Sanatani's, "The Little Light!" It gives the reader a glimpse of the author's journey with personal anecdotes and stories, along with some useful tips for those looking to self-publish. While mainly applicable for those in the publishing business, some portions are clearly relatable for those who have operated or worked in a start-up. It covers some of the internal battles faced by many entrepreneurs and those in the startup industry, making it a book that can identify with those outside of the publishing industry. <br /><br />It intertwines building a business with personal challenges of identity, culture, finding oneself through ancestral heritage and all the other adventures that life has to offer. This book will speak to those who may have never felt a full belonging in one place, or those uprooted from their original heritage, making them seek answers to what "home" really means. <br /><br />All in all, it's shows us how life's journey makes sense backwards, and that the challenges are a part and not a definition of what's to come. Plus, you learn a bit more about the world, civilisation and history trivia as you turn the pages! <br /><br />Way to go Dipa Sanatani! Waiting for the next one - after this deserving entrepreneur gets some rest of course!<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4027128347224059639" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
